{
  "texts": [
    "These claims suggest that ChatGPT can engage students in real-time conversations, provide personalized guidance and support that is relevant and contextually appropriate, and adapt its interactions based on the specific needs and preferences of individual learners (Fadhil & Gabrielli, 2017; Zhai, 2022).",
    "This paper proposes a framework for examining the personalization capabilities of current ChatGPT technologies, focusing on various levels of personalized learning (PL).",
    "It also presents an empirical study that investigates interactions between graduate students and a ChatGPT-based chatbot.",
    "In the remainder of this paper, we refer to this bot as a 'tutor bot' since it primarily serves that role.",
    "Fifty-one graduate students participated in one-on-one tutoring sessions with the bot, focusing on the topic of educational reforms."
  ]
}